s, traces the Canadian/British/Native side of the conflict (amid a literature dominated by the American view), and casts new light on an allied military strategy that very nearly succeeded, but when it failed, failed spectacularly.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077357405240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773574052423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773574052/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles